parsed.title: Foundation
parsed.summary: Set in the distant future, "Foundation" tells the saga of a group of scientists led by the visionary Hari Seldon. Seldon, employing the science of psychohistory, which combines history, sociology, and statistical mathematics, foresees the imminent fall of the mighty Galactic Empire. He devises a plan to reduce the ensuing dark age by establishing the Foundation, an organization designed to preserve and expand human knowledge. The novel navigates the political and social intricacies faced by the Foundation as it strives to ensure the swift revival of a new Empire and the enduring prosperity of all humanity.
parsed.author: Isaac Asimov
